name: market for potato seed, for setting | potato seed, for setting | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/9186/documentation

This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for  'potato seed, for setting', in the Global geography.;This market contains no transport or losses, as they are irrelevant for the delivered product.;The product 'potato seed, for setting' is a seed. It is an annual crop. The seed produced at the farm is transported to the processing centre, treated (pre-cleaning, cleaning, eventually drying, chemical dressing (for integrated production) and bag filling), stored and afterwards transported to the regional storage centre.

This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce 'potato seed, for setting',  within the geography of Global.

This activity ends with the supply of  potato seed, for setting', to the consumers of this product. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.
